11/12/2006
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Smaller parties in parliament -- the New Social Democratic Party, VMRO-NP, the Liberal Democratic Party and the Liberal Party -- want to be included in the newly launched political dialogue process in Macedonia, according to separate statements issued at the weekend. The parties say they should be treated as equal partners and should participate in all future meetings. These sessions had been restricted to representatives of the four main parties -- the ruling VMRO-DPMNE and Democratic Party of Albanians, and the opposition Social Democratic Alliance of Macedonia and Democratic Union for Integration. (Vecer - 11/12/06; Utrinski Vesnik, Makfax - 09/12/06)
